                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/830: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-27T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>158. Your 283, June 24, 5 p.m.</p>
                <p>Resolution to remit remainder of the indemnity passed the Senate last summer.</p>
                <p>It is understood that Foreign Affairs Committee of the House of Representatives
                    favorably disposed, but Chairman of the Committee believes that chances of
                    passage of the resolution through the House would be enhanced if action should
                    be deferred until December session of Congress.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
